Variable name:  #3, \hfill\break
Default value: #4, {Range: #5} \\
#6
}
%
%  Table Columns
\def\columns{\subsubsection{Columns}
The order of the columns is arbitrary.
Allowed data types are:
{\bf I}=16 bit integer, {\bf J}=32 bit integer, 
{\bf E}=real, {\bf D}=double, 
{\bf C}=Complex (32 bit each), {\bf M}=double complex (64 bit each), 
{\bf A}=character, 
{\bf L}=logical, {\bf X=}bit array, {\bf B}=byte array.
Multidimensional arrays use the {\tt TDIMnnn} keyword
convention.\hfill\break
The first line of each entry gives the name:type, units and
dimensionality of the entry.
``Variable name'' is the name the keyword is given in software,
possibly with a suffix if the column label ends in \#xxx where xxx is
a keyword.
\begin{itemize}}
\def\endcolumns{\end{itemize}}
